  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"aphelios","win":["Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Aphelios","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aphelios owns this window: with the right gun pairing (Calibrum root or Severum lifesteal into Gravitum) he out-DPSes your unstacked Q and can chunk you off any greedy last-hit, so you farm from max range and only trade with your W poke when his guns are on the weak side."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R is up but so is his Moonlight Vigil, and with only a handful of Dragon Practice stacks your ult is a weak nuke; don't force an all-in yet, use R to secure a fleeing kill or peel, not to open a fair fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where you flip it: once your first item lands and your stacks climb, your Q upgrade starts to melt, and you outrange his short-magazine guns while kiting Gravitum slows behind minions."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 100+ stacks your Q one-shots waves and pokes, R becomes a lane-crossing execute, and you simply outrange and out-scale everything Aphelios threatens if you space his root and CC."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach your stack breakpoints untaxed by farming safely","Fight after your first item when Q upgrade online","Kite behind minions to dodge Calibrum roots and Gravitum"],"foe":["Punish you levels 1-5 while his gun rotation out-trades you","Land Calibrum root or Ardent Gravitum to lock an all-in","Snowball an early lead before your scaling arrives"]},"early":"Aphelios starts stronger: his opening gun pairing out-damages your zero-stack Q, so respect the level 1-2 window, hug your minions and only step up to secure CS or land a safe W poke when his guns are on cooldown or the weak color.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his: Calibrum roots and Severum sustain let him win extended trades, and even with R at 6 your thin stack count makes your ult a soft nuke, so keep farming toward your item and stack breakpoints rather than dueling.","late":"Once your first item completes and stacks pile up the lane inverts hard; your upgraded Q shreds, R turns into a screen-wide execute, and you outrange his short magazines, so space his root and let scaling close it out.","whys":["Aphelios's level 1 gun pairing out-trades your unstacked Q auto damage.","At level 2 his second gun and ammo economy still beat your poke.","Level 3 Calibrum roots and Severum sustain win his extended trades.","Through 4-5 his rotating guns keep out-DPSing your low-stack kit.","At 6 Moonlight Vigil plus his guns beat your weak early ult and stacks.","Your first item plus climbing stacks flips the DPS and range advantage to you.","With 2+ items your stacked Q and R out-scale and outrange everything he has."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"ashe","win":["Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Ashe","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ashe dominates this stretch: her permanent Frost Shot slow means every auto she lands sticks you in place while she kites, and with a support she can chain-slow you off CS and win any short trade before your Q is stacked."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Enchanted Crystal Arrow is a global lane threat; a landed R stun into her Volley plus support CC can outright kill your squishy early Smolder, so hold your E dash to break the follow-up and don't stand in the open."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item plus stacks let your upgraded Q trade back through her slow, and you start to outrange her non-ulted poke while farming toward the point where her lane pressure stops mattering."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully stacked you out-scale Ashe hard: your Q melts, R crosses the map as an execute, and while she brings utility her raw DPS can't keep pace, so respect the arrow and win the scaling race."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely to your stack breakpoints under her slow","Use E to dodge Volley and disengage her kite","Outscale her once first item and Q upgrade land"],"foe":["Perma-slow you with Frost Shot to win every trade","Land R stun into Volley plus support for an all-in","Snowball the early lead her utility creates"]},"early":"Ashe wins the opening: her Frost Shot slows on every auto, so she can walk you down and out-trade your zero-stack Q while denying your last-hits, meaning you farm passively at max range and only step up when her Volley is down.","mid":"Levels 3-6 remain hers; the permanent slow chains into support CC and her level 6 Crystal Arrow gives a point-and-click stun all-in that can delete early Smolder, so play behind minions, save E to break the combo, and keep stacking.","late":"After your first item completes and stacks climb you flip it: upgraded Q trades through the slow, R becomes a lane-crossing execute, and your scaling simply outgrows Ashe's utility-heavy but low-ceiling damage.","whys":["Ashe's Frost Shot slow lets her kite and out-trade you at level 1.","Level 2 Volley plus perma-slow keeps her ahead in the poke war.","At 3 her chained slows win extended trades against your unstacked kit.","Through 4-5 her slow into support CC keeps you pinned and behind.","Level 6 Crystal Arrow stun all-in can kill your squishy early Smolder.","Your first item and Q upgrade flip trades and range back to you.","Fully stacked, your Q and R execute out-scale Ashe's utility damage."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"caitlyn","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Smolder","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Caitlyn's range-bully window but it's playable: she out-ranges your autos and her Yordle Snap Trap plus Piltover Peacemaker headshot combo punishes bad positioning, so dodge traps, last-hit from behind minions, and don't let her zone you off stacks; play it even and you stay on curve."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R comes online and tilts the lane your way: while her Ace in the Hole is a pick tool, your ult plus enough stacks lets you burst back or answer her all-in, and you no longer have to respect her lane bully as hard."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item spike beats hers: Caitlyn's power is front-loaded and fades, while your upgraded Q starts shredding, so you trade back through her traps and out-DPS her in any committed fight."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully stacked you leave her behind entirely; your Q melts, R executes across the lane, and Caitlyn's static range advantage means nothing once your damage and effective range balloon past hers."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge traps and farm even through the lane-bully phase","Hit level 6 and first item to flip the DPS","Reach late where stacked Q and R outclass her"],"foe":["Zone you off CS with superior auto range early","Land trap plus Peacemaker headshot combos","Poke you down before your scaling arrives"]},"early":"It's a skill matchup early: Caitlyn out-ranges your autos and her trap-headshot combo threatens punishment, but Smolder's safe farm and W poke keep it even if you respect her range, dodge Yordle Snap Traps, and last-hit patiently from behind the minion line.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay a coin-flip of positioning until your ult lands; play around her trap cooldowns, don't get caught by Peacemaker, and once you hit 6 with stacks the lane starts tilting to you as her early bully loses teeth.","late":"From first item onward you take over: Caitlyn's front-loaded power fades while your upgraded Q shreds and R becomes a lane-crossing execute, so your scaling simply outgrows her static range edge.","whys":["Level 1 is even: her range bullies but your safe farm holds.","At 2 trap and Peacemaker threaten, but good spacing keeps it skill.","Level 3 stays a positioning coin-flip around her cooldowns.","Through 4-5 dodging traps keeps the lane even before your spike.","At 6 your R and stacks flip the lane in your favor.","Your first-item Q upgrade out-DPSes her fading front-loaded kit.","Fully stacked, your Q and R execute outclass her static range edge."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"corki","win":["Corki","Corki","Corki","Corki","Corki","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Corki out-trades you here: his Phosphorus Bomb and Gatling Gun shred through your unstacked Q, and once he has The Package or just his mixed-damage autos he wins every extended trade, so farm from range and only poke with W when his Bomb is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Missile Barrage gives him wave-clear and poke that out-pressures your weak early ult; your R at low stacks is a soft nuke, so don't force fights, respect his Valkyrie escape, and keep collecting CS toward your spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item flips it hard: while Corki also spikes on items, your stacking Q scales past his flat damage, and your upgraded auto-empowered burst out-trades him once you're online."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully stacked you dwarf Corki: your Q melts and R executes across the lane, and his true-damage mix and Missile poke can't match your ceiling once your stacks are maxed."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely to stack breakpoints past his early bully","Trade back once first item and Q upgrade land","Outscale his flat damage in the late game"],"foe":["Out-trade you 3-5 with Bomb and Gatling shred","Poke with Missile Barrage and roam via The Package","Snowball his early item spike before you scale"]},"early":"Corki wins the opening: his Phosphorus Bomb burst and mixed-damage autos out-trade your zero-stack Q, so you respect his level 1-2 poke, hug minions, and only step out to secure last-hits or land a safe W when his Bomb is on cooldown.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his; Gatling Gun and Missile Barrage out-DPS and out-poke you, The Package threatens roams, and your low-stack ult can't answer his pressure, so keep farming and scaling toward your first-item breakpoint.","late":"Once your first item lands the lane inverts; your stacking Q outscales his flat mixed damage, R becomes a lane-crossing execute, and by full stacks Corki simply can't match your damage ceiling.","whys":["Corki's Phosphorus Bomb and autos out-trade your unstacked kit at level 1.","At 2 his mixed-damage poke keeps him ahead in trades.","Level 3 Gatling Gun shreds you in every extended trade.","Through 4-5 his poke and The Package pressure keep you behind.","At 6 Missile Barrage out-pressures your weak low-stack ult.","Your first-item Q upgrade outscales his flat damage and flips trades.","Fully stacked, your Q and R execute dwarf his damage ceiling."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"draven","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Smolder","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Draven's Spinning Axe damage is terrifying but it's a skill lane: if he commits to catching axes he over-extends, so you can W-poke him and last-hit safely while he chases his axe pickups; don't stand for a Stand Aside knock-up all-in and it stays even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R comes online and answers his snowball: while Whirling Death is a long-range execute, your ult plus stacks lets you burst back or peel his all-in, so you stop having to fear every axe-fueled trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item spike beats his tempo: Draven's economy relies on staying ahead, and once your Q upgrade shreds you out-DPS him in a straight fight and deny the snowball he needs."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully stacked you crush Draven: your Q melts and R executes across the lane, and if he hasn't already snowballed, his flat axe damage falls far behind your scaling ceiling."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny axe catches and farm even through his early","Reach 6 and first item to flip the trades","Outscale him if the game goes long"],"foe":["Snowball early off Spinning Axe damage","Land Stand Aside knock-up into a support all-in","End the game before your stacks come online"]},"early":"It's a skill matchup: Draven's Spinning Axes hit like a truck, but catching them pulls him out of position, so you punish greedy axe pickups with W poke and safe last-hits; respect his all-in with Stand Aside and it stays even.","mid":"Levels 3-6 hinge on trading discipline; don't feed his axe economy or eat a knock-up all-in, and once you hit 6 with stacks your ult answers his snowball and the lane tips your way as his early lead window closes.","late":"From first item onward you take over: Draven needs an early snowball to matter, and if you denied it your upgraded Q shreds while R executes across the lane, leaving his flat damage far behind your scaling.","whys":["Level 1 is even: his axe damage scares you but greedy catches over-extend him.","At 2 disciplined trading keeps it skill against his axe economy.","Level 3 stays even if you deny axe pickups and dodge his all-in.","Through 4-5 punishing his over-extends keeps the lane balanced.","At 6 your R and stacks answer his snowball and flip the lane.","Your first-item Q upgrade out-DPSes his tempo-reliant kit.","Fully stacked, your Q and R execute crush his flat axe damage."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"ezreal","win":["Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Ezreal","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ezreal owns this window with Mystic Shot poke: he pokes you off CS from max range and his Arcane Shift makes him hard to punish, so you last-hit behind minions to body-block his Q and only trade W back when his E is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Trueshot Barrage adds global poke and finishing pressure while your low-stack R is still a soft nuke, so don't force an all-in; farm through his poke, use E to dodge Mystic Shots, and keep your stack count climbing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item flips the DPS: Ezreal is poke-and-scale but relies on landing skillshots, and once your Q upgrade shreds you out-trade him hard whenever you close the gap behind minions."},{"when":"Late","text":"Fully stacked you out-scale Ezreal comfortably; your Q melts and R executes across the lane, and his poke damage can't keep pace with your damage ceiling once your stacks are maxed."}],"wants":{"you":["Body-block Mystic Shot with minions and farm safe","Reach first item and Q upgrade to out-trade","Outscale his poke in the late game"],"foe":["Poke you off CS with Mystic Shot from max range","Stay safe with Arcane Shift while chunking you","Out-poke and scale before your stacks arrive"]},"early":"Ezreal wins the opening: Mystic Shot pokes you off last-hits from range and Arcane Shift keeps him safe from punishment, so you hug the minion line to body-block his Q and only step out for CS or a W poke when his E is down.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay his; his poke chips you down while you can't safely commit, and even at 6 your low-stack ult can't answer his Trueshot pressure, so keep farming, dodge Mystic Shots with your dash, and scale toward your item.","late":"Once your first item completes the lane inverts; your upgraded Q shreds and R becomes a lane-crossing execute, and Ezreal's poke-reliant damage simply can't match your stacked ceiling.","whys":["Ezreal's Mystic Shot pokes you off CS from range at level 1.","At 2 his poke plus Arcane Shift safety keeps him ahead.","Level 3 his Q poke chunks you before you can trade back.","Through 4-5 his safe poke keeps you behind and farming passively.","At 6 Trueshot pressure beats your weak low-stack ult.","Your first-item Q upgrade flips the DPS and out-trades his poke.","Fully stacked, your Q and R execute out-scale his poke damage."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Heimerdinger","Heimerdinger","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q Super Scorcher Breath pokes over the minion wall, but Heimerdinger's H-28G Turrets zone the same space and punish you if you walk up to last-hit under them. Farm from max range, let your support soak turret aggro, and only step forward when a grenade is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Heimerdinger's UPGRADE!!! ult turns a single turret into a beam cannon or an empowered E stun, giving him an all-in you cannot walk into. You have no burst yet and only 4-8 Q stacks, so this is his strongest window and you must respect the CH-3X Lightning Grenade stun."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish first item and pass ~35-40 Dragon Practice stacks, your Q flames start to arc and your W Acherontia Hunt lets you dash through minions to close range. You outrange his turrets on poke and can shove waves faster than he can rebuild them."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped Q with true-range flame spread and W execute shreds his turrets and his squishy body instantly; his zone control means nothing once you can one-shot the whole wave and flame-jump on top of him in a teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach ~35+ Dragon Practice stacks so Q spreads flames and clears turrets for free","A support with hard engage or a gap-closer to punish him when his grenade is down","Long-range items and lane priority so you scale past his level 5-6 zone spike"],"foe":["Keep all three H-28G Turrets alive to wall off your last-hitting and poke","Land CH-3X Lightning Grenade stuns to set up his UPGRADE!!! all-in at 6","Deny your early stacks by zoning you off the minion wall with turret damage"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even and skill-dependent: Heimerdinger has not fully set up his turret field yet, so you can contest CS and land the odd Q poke, but stepping into turret range costs you. Play for safe stacks and don't feed his poke.","mid":"Levels 3-6 tilt to Heimerdinger. A full turret line plus his grenade stun zones you off the wave and denies your Dragon Practice stacks, and his level 6 UPGRADE!!! all-in threatens to delete you while you still lack burst. Farm at max range and never facecheck a grenade.","late":"Once you complete first item and stack Q past the arc threshold, the matchup flips hard to you. Your true-ranged flame spread clears his turrets instantly and W lets you jump onto his fragile frame, so by 2+ items you outscale and out-range everything he does.","whys":["Level 1 is even because neither of you has a real spike and it comes down to who wins the CS trade.","Level 2 stays skill-based since his turret field is incomplete and your poke can trade evenly.","Level 3 remains a coin-flip as his zone is only half-built and you can still contest the wave.","Levels 4-5 are still even until his full turret line comes online and starts denying you.","Level 5-6 favours Heimerdinger because a complete turret field plus grenade stun zones your stacking.","At level 6 Heimerdinger's UPGRADE!!! all-in can burst you before your Q stacks give you any burst back.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame-spread Q and W execute obliterate his turrets and squishy body, flipping it to you."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"jhin","win":["Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Jhin","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jhin's W Deadly Flourish and root-off-CC combo make walking up to last-hit dangerous, and his fourth-shot crit plus Q Dancing Grenade out-trades you at every window. You have almost no burst and are stacking Dragon Practice, so respect his auto rhythm and only step in when he is mid-reload."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Jhin's Curtain Call ult snipes you from screen-away and finishes anyone your support has slowed; your level 6 Q upgrade gives you range but not the burst to punish him yet. This is squarely his window and you should position so a Curtain Call bullet always has a minion or wall to eat."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even at first item Jhin stays ahead on lane pressure: his crit-scaling autos and W root deny your walk-ups while you are still building Dragon Practice stacks toward the flame-arc threshold. Farm safely and prioritize stacks over trades."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped Q with true-range flame spread and W Acherontia Hunt execute finally overtake his fixed four-shot pattern; you can flame-jump onto his immobile frame and one-shot him before he reloads or lands a root."}],"wants":{"you":["Stack Dragon Practice safely past the ~35 arc threshold so your Q spreads flames","A support who blocks or cleanses his W root and Curtain Call snipes","Reach 2+ items where your scaling execute beats his fixed four-shot burst"],"foe":["Land W Deadly Flourish roots off support CC to lock you for a full combo","Use his fourth-shot crit and Q bounce to win every early trade","Snipe you with Curtain Call from range while you lack burst to answer"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Jhin: his auto damage is front-loaded and his Q Dancing Grenade pokes you off the wave while you have no stacks and no burst. Play safe, soak CS at range, and never contest a trade into his loaded fourth shot.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Jhin's: W Deadly Flourish roots you off any support CC, his crit autos out-trade you, and at 6 Curtain Call threatens you from across the lane. You are still stacking Dragon Practice, so farm passively and avoid giving him a root target.","late":"By first item Jhin's lane lead persists, but once you pass the flame-arc stack threshold and hit 2+ items the matchup flips. Your uncapped true-ranged Q and W execute delete his immobile body, and you can flame-jump on top of him faster than he can reload.","whys":["Level 1 favours Jhin because his front-loaded auto damage wins the opening trade.","Level 2 stays Jhin's as his Q poke chips you while you have no stacks to answer.","Level 3 favours Jhin since W Deadly Flourish gives him a root-combo you can't match.","Levels 4-5 remain Jhin's on the back of his crit fourth-shot out-trading your farm phase.","Level 5-6 favours Jhin because his crit autos and W root still dominate your walk-ups.","Level 6 favours Jhin as Curtain Call snipes you from range while you still lack burst.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame-spread Q and W execute overtake his fixed pattern and flip it to you."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"jinx","win":["Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Jinx","Smolder","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jinx's rockets Switcheroo give her AoE range and wave clear that pushes you under tower and lets her poke your walk-ups, while her W Zap! slow sets up her support's engage. You are stacking Dragon Practice with no burst, so last-hit carefully under tower and only trade when her rockets are on their mana-heavy pattern."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Jinx's Super Mega Death Rocket! gives her a global finisher and her Get Excited! resets punish anyone caught, but your level 6 Q upgrade starts closing the gap. It's still her window early, so respect the ult snipe and keep minions between you until your stacks come online."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where you flip it: passing ~35 Dragon Practice stacks makes your Q arc and spread flames, and at first item you shove waves and out-range her minigun. Jinx is immobile, so W Acherontia Hunt plus support CC turns her into a free kill."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute out-DPS and out-range her rocket form; she needs resets to come online but you delete her before she gets the first one. Space behind your frontline and flame-jump onto her the moment she's exposed."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the first four levels and stack Dragon Practice past the flame-arc threshold","Punish her immobility with W Acherontia Hunt and support CC once you spike","Reach first item where you out-range and out-shove her minigun and rockets"],"foe":["Use rockets Switcheroo to shove you under tower and deny early stacks","Land W Zap! slows to set up her support's engage while you lack escape","Get an early kill or reset with Get Excited! before your item spike lands"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 favour Jinx: her rocket range and W Zap! slow let her control the wave, push you in, and poke your last-hits while you have no burst and are grinding Dragon Practice stacks. Farm safely under tower and don't give her support a slow to engage on.","mid":"The matchup flips around level 5: once you approach the flame-arc stack threshold your Q clears waves and out-ranges her, and her total lack of mobility means W plus any support CC kills her. Start pressuring her walk-ups as your damage ramps.","late":"By first item and especially 2+ items you hard-outscale Jinx. Your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute delete her before she stacks Get Excited! resets, so space behind your frontline and flame-jump the instant she's caught out of position.","whys":["Level 1 favours Jinx because her rocket range lets her poke and control the wave.","Level 2 stays Jinx's as Switcheroo rockets shove you in and deny walk-ups.","Level 3 favours Jinx since W Zap! slow sets up trades and support engages.","Level 4 remains Jinx's on wave control while you still lack burst and stacks.","Level 5-6 flips to Smolder as your Q nears the flame-arc threshold and out-ranges her.","At first item you out-shove and punish her immobility with W and support CC.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame Q and W execute hard-outscale her rocket form."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"kaisa","win":["Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Kai'Sa","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kai'Sa's Q Icathian Rain and passive plasma stacking let her burst you in a short window, and her W Void Seeker poke chips you from range as you last-hit. You have no burst and are stacking Dragon Practice, so play behind minions to block Void Seekers and don't let her stack plasma on you for the ranged W execute."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kai'Sa's Killer Instinct ult gives her a gap-close all-in onto you the moment her support lands CC, and her plasma pop empowers her E stealth-steroid burst. Your level 6 Q upgrade helps but you still lack the burst to answer, so ward flanks and keep W Acherontia Hunt ready to disengage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is your flip point: past ~35 Dragon Practice stacks your Q arcs and spreads flames, and at first item you out-range her Q and shove her in. If she dashes onto you with Killer Instinct, W plus support CC punishes her for overcommitting."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute out-range and out-DPS her; she must dive into your frontline to deal damage, and your flame-jump plus a peeling support turns her all-in into a quick death before her shield and stealth save her."}],"wants":{"you":["Block W Void Seeker pokes with minions and deny her plasma stacks early","Reach ~35 Dragon Practice stacks so your Q out-ranges her Q burst","Punish her Killer Instinct dive with W Acherontia Hunt and support CC"],"foe":["Stack plasma with Q and passive to unlock her ranged W execute on you","Land Void Seeker pokes to whittle you down during the stacking phase","Use Killer Instinct at 6 to all-in you before your item spike arrives"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 lean Kai'Sa: her Q Icathian Rain trades hard and Void Seeker pokes you off the wave while you have no burst and are grinding Dragon Practice. Farm from behind minions to eat her W and never let plasma stacks build to the execute threshold.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Kai'Sa's: plasma-empowered bursts and her level 6 Killer Instinct give her an all-in you can't yet answer, especially into support CC. Play safe, keep W ready to reposition, and prioritize stacks over risky trades.","late":"Once you complete first item and pass the flame-arc stack threshold the matchup flips to you. Your uncapped true-ranged flame Q out-ranges her Q, and W plus a peeling support punishes every Killer Instinct dive, so by 2+ items you out-scale her hard.","whys":["Level 1 favours Kai'Sa because her Q trade and early plasma pressure beat your stack phase.","Level 2 stays Kai'Sa's as Void Seeker poke chips you while you lack burst.","Level 3 favours Kai'Sa since plasma stacking unlocks her ranged W execute threat.","Levels 4-5 remain Kai'Sa's on the strength of her empowered E burst window.","Level 5 stays Kai'Sa's as her all-in potential outweighs your still-building damage.","At level 6 Killer Instinct gives Kai'Sa a dive all-in before your item spike lands... but once you complete first item and stack Q, it flips to Smolder.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame Q and W execute out-range and punish her dive-reliant kit."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"kalista","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kalista","Kalista","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kalista's Pierce spear and Rend stacking let her poke and detonate for big chunks, and her hop-on-every-attack mobility makes her hard to pin while you last-hit. You have no burst and are stacking Dragon Practice, so trade only when her Rend stacks are low and use minions to body-block her spears."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Kalista's Fate's Call ult lets her support dive you and reset a hard engage, turning her level 6 into a strong all-in window while your Q upgrade gives range but not enough burst to punish. Respect the ult engage, keep W Acherontia Hunt to escape, and don't overstay in range of her Rend detonation."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kalista's Rend-plus-item spike still out-duels you in a straight trade at first item, but you're close to the flip: past ~35 Dragon Practice stacks your Q begins to arc. Prioritize stacks over trades and let her overextend her mobility into your support's CC."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute overtake her Rend scaling; she relies on repositioning and support setup, but your flame-jump and AoE spread punish her the moment she's stuck attacking. You out-DPS and out-range her once your stacks mature."}],"wants":{"you":["Body-block Pierce spears with minions and avoid feeding Rend stacks","Grind Dragon Practice past the flame-arc threshold before committing","Punish an overextended Fate's Call dive with W and support CC"],"foe":["Stack Rend and detonate for burst during your weak stacking phase","Use constant attack-hops to dodge your Q and stay untargetable","Set up a Fate's Call dive at 6 to all-in before your item spike"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are even and skill-based: Kalista's spear poke and Rend threat are real, but her low base durability means a fed Dragon Practice start and good minion-blocking keep the lane close. Farm safely, dodge spears behind the wave, and don't let Rend stacks pile up.","mid":"Levels 5-6 tilt to Kalista: her Rend detonation and Fate's Call ult give her a support-diving all-in you can't match while you still lack burst. Keep W ready to disengage, respect the ult engage, and prioritize stacks over risky trades.","late":"Once you clear first item and pass the flame-arc stack threshold the matchup flips to you. Your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute out-range and out-DPS her Rend scaling, so by 2+ items you punish her whenever she's locked into an attack animation.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both of you trade cautiously and it comes down to CS and spear-dodging.","Level 2 stays skill-based since neither has a decisive spike yet.","Level 3 remains even because her Rend stacks are still building and you can body-block spears.","Level 4 is a coin-flip that hinges on who lands poke and dodges better.","Level 5 favours Kalista as her Rend detonation burst outpaces your stack phase.","At level 6 Fate's Call gives Kalista a support-dive all-in before your item spike.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame Q and W execute overtake her Rend scaling and flip it to you."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"karthus","win":["Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Karthus","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karthus bot spams Q Lay Waste to poke you off every last-hit and his E Defile plus wall Wall of Pain zone you when you walk up. You have no burst and are stacking Dragon Practice, so soak CS at max range, dodge Q by side-stepping between casts, and don't fight in his E aura."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Karthus's Requiem gives him a global execute that finishes you from anywhere the moment you're low, and his passive Death Defied lets him keep casting Q after he dies. Your level 6 Q upgrade adds range but not burst, so play at healthy HP and never let a poke war leave you executable to Requiem."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is your flip: past ~35 Dragon Practice stacks your Q arcs and spreads flames, out-ranging his Lay Waste and shoving him in. Karthus is completely immobile, so W Acherontia Hunt plus support CC turns him into a free kill once you close the gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your uncapped true-ranged flame Q and W execute out-DPS his poke and delete his stationary body before he can channel Requiem. Space so his Wall of Pain can't peel you, then flame-jump on top of him and burst him out before Death Defied matters."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Lay Waste between casts and stay out of his E Defile aura","Stack Dragon Practice past the flame-arc threshold to out-range his poke","Punish his total immobility with W Acherontia Hunt and support CC"],"foe":["Spam Q Lay Waste to deny your last-hits and chip you during stacking","Keep you low enough for a Requiem execute after any poke war","Use Wall of Pain to slow your walk-ups and protect his fragile body"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Karthus: his Q Lay Waste out-ranges your comfortable last-hitting and pokes you off the wave while you have no burst and are grinding Dragon Practice. Farm at max range, side-step his Q between casts, and stay out of E Defile.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Karthus's: relentless Q poke plus his level 6 Requiem global execute mean any poke war can end with you dead from across the map. Keep your HP healthy, dodge diligently, and prioritize stacks over trading into his aura.","late":"Once you complete first item and pass the flame-arc stack threshold the matchup flips hard. Your uncapped true-ranged flame Q out-ranges Lay Waste and W punishes his total immobility, so by 2+ items you flame-jump on and delete him before Requiem or Death Defied ever matter.","whys":["Level 1 favours Karthus because Lay Waste out-ranges your last-hitting from the start.","Level 2 stays Karthus's as his Q poke denies stacks while you lack burst.","Level 3 favours Karthus since E Defile and continued Q zoning control the wave.","Levels 4-5 remain Karthus's on the strength of his relentless ranged poke.","Level 5-6 favours Karthus as Requiem threatens a global execute after any poke war.","At level 6 his Requiem plus poke keep you executable from across the map... until your item spike arrives.","By 2+ items your uncapped flame Q and W execute out-range his poke and delete his immobile body."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"kogmaw","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Smolder","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Neither of you wants to brawl early: both are stacking scaling passives, so the lane is a farm race where you last-hit with autos and poke Q stacks off the wave. Kog'Maw's W (Bio-Arcane Barrage) gives him big auto range but drains mana fast, so respect his all-in only if his support has hard CC to hold you in the caustic-spit zone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You get Mounting Flames as a real teamfight/execute threat while Kog'Maw's ult (Living Artillery) is just a poke/waveclear tool with a mana-ramping cost. Your Q building toward the 225-stack execute means you out-threaten his squishy, immobile frame; if he over-extends to siege, punish with a W dash-in and cash out a big Q."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Both spike hard at one item, but your Q stacks compound so a completed first item plus stack count lets you shred Kog'Maw before his on-hit ramp matters in a straight 2v2. He has zero mobility and his only peel is the passive Icathian Surprise on death, so once you hit stack thresholds you win the standing DPS race."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is a scaling mirror where your execute Q and Achooo! reposition beat a stationary Kog'Maw. Space so his support can't flank, focus him first in fights, and your compounding stacks turn every skirmish into a one-shot on his no-escape body."}],"wants":{"you":["A clean farm race so your Dragon Practice stacks and Q count ramp uncontested","Fights after level 6 where Mounting Flames and stack thresholds are online","A support with CC to lock Kog'Maw's immobile body for the kill"],"foe":["To poke you down safely with Living Artillery from max range","To reach full on-hit build (Guinsoo/BorK) and get peeled all game","A disengage/peel support so his no-mobility frame survives your all-in"]},"early":"Both of you are scaling passives, so levels 1-2 are a pure last-hit and light-poke race with no real all-in; trade autos for CS and don't burn summoners over a wave. It's even and skill-based who farms cleaner.","mid":"Once you hit 6 your execute Q and Mounting Flames give you a kill threat Kog'Maw's Living Artillery can't match; his mana-hungry ult only pokes. Punish any greedy siege position with a W dash and a stacked Q.","late":"With one-plus items your compounding stacks out-race his on-hit ramp against an immobile target; focus him first, use Achooo! to reposition, and cash the 225-stack execute in every fight.","whys":["Level 1 is an even farm race between two scaling passives with no combat spike for either.","Level 2 stays skill-based: both trade autos for CS and neither has an all-in.","Level 3 remains even as both stack scaling passives rather than committing to a fight.","Levels 4-5 are still a coin-flip farm race decided by who last-hits and pokes cleaner.","At 6 your Mounting Flames execute and Q stack threat out-pressure Kog'Maw's mana-hungry Living Artillery, tilting the lane to you.","At one item your compounding Q stacks shred his immobile frame faster than his on-hit ramp comes online.","With two-plus items your execute Q and Achooo! reposition dominate a no-mobility Kog'Maw in every skirmish."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"lucian","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Lucian","Lucian","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian wants to dash in with E (Relentless Pursuit) and unload his Lightslinger double-tap plus Q (Piercing Light) through minions, out-trading your low early stack count. Stand behind your caster minions so his Q can't line you up, only step to CS, and let your support screen his all-in; you're a scaling stacker, not an early duelist."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Lucian's Culling ult plus his dash mobility give him a real all-in and burst window while your Mounting Flames is online but your stacks aren't threatening yet. He can E in, chunk you, and E-reset out before you cash a big Q, so play safe and don't get caught in the dash range without peel."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Lucian's peak: his first-item spike (Essence Reaver/Navori) makes his double-tap and Q rotations delete you before your stacks mature. Farm from max range, use Achooo! only to disengage his dash, and survive this window rather than contesting the 2v2."},{"when":"Late","text":"The lane flips hard once your Q stacks near the 225 execute and you out-range his fixed-range kit. Lucian falls off as your compounding damage and Achooo! kiting let you shred him from safety; space behind frontline and he can no longer dash-burst you down."}],"wants":{"you":["To survive the early-to-mid dash-burst window and reach stack maturity","Farming from max range behind minions so his Q can't pierce onto you","Late fights where your execute Q and kiting out-range his fixed-range burst"],"foe":["Short trades where he dashes in, double-taps, and E-resets out","His first-item spike to burst you before your stacks compound","A CC or engage support to hold you still for the Culling all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill-based but Lucian holds the trading edge with his dash and double-tap; you're stacking, so only step up to last-hit and stay behind casters so his Piercing Light can't line you. Don't contest his early aggression, respect the E mobility.","mid":"At 6 through his first item Lucian is ahead: Culling plus E-reset burst you before your stacks threaten, so farm safe and disengage his dashes with Achooo!. This is his window, survive it rather than fight it.","late":"With two-plus items and a maturing Q execute you flip the matchup, out-ranging his fixed kit and kiting his dashes; space behind your frontline and shred him before he closes.","whys":["Level 1 is even and skill-based before Lucian's dash-trade pattern comes online.","Level 2 stays a coin-flip as neither has a committal all-in yet.","Level 3 remains skill-based though Lucian's double-tap starts edging trades.","Levels 4-5 stay close but hinge on you dodging his Q line rather than either snowballing.","At 6 Lucian's Culling and E-reset give him a burst all-in your immature stacks can't answer.","At one item Lucian peaks, deleting you before your Q stacks compound.","With two-plus items your maturing execute Q and kiting out-range Lucian's fixed-range burst and flip the lane."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"missfortune","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Miss Fortune","Miss Fortune","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Miss Fortune wants to auto-poke you, proc her passive movement-speed off a switched target, and chunk you with Q (Double Up) bouncing off a minion onto you. Break line of sight of her Q by not standing directly behind a low minion, only step to CS, and let your support absorb the poke since your stacks aren't a threat yet."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Bootleg RFC into Bullet Time gives Miss Fortune a lane-controlling ult: if her support lands CC she can channel Strut of Make It Rain to zone and burst you in the 2v2. Your Mounting Flames is up but stacks are thin, so respect her ult all-in, hold a Achooo! to reposition out of the cone, and don't get pinned."},{"when":"1st item","text":"MF's first-item poke build snowballs her lane-bully pattern, letting her siege and chip you below your comfortable farm range before your Q count matters. Sustain up, farm from max distance, and dodge Double Up lines; survive this window rather than dueling her head-on."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale her hard: your compounding Q toward the 225 execute and Achooo! kiting beat MF's stationary channel. In fights sidestep or LoS her Bullet Time, focus her squishy body, and your matured stacks delete her before the channel pays off."}],"wants":{"you":["To weather her early poke and reach stack maturity","Farming from max range so Double Up can't bounce onto you","Late fights where you sidestep Bullet Time and out-scale her poke"],"foe":["To poke and bully with Double Up and passive movement speed","A CC support to lock you inside a channeled Bullet Time","Her first-item spike to siege you off the wave before stacks mature"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill-based but Miss Fortune is the natural lane bully with Double Up poke; you're stacking, so dodge her Q bounce by minion positioning and only step to last-hit. Don't trade into her poke, scale.","mid":"From 6 through her first item MF holds the edge: Bullet Time plus support CC can zone and burst you while your stacks are thin. Respect the ult all-in, hold Achooo! to escape the cone, and farm safe.","late":"With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting out-scale her stationary channel; LoS or sidestep Bullet Time, focus her squishy frame, and matured stacks close it out.","whys":["Level 1 is even before MF's poke pattern establishes lane control.","Level 2 stays skill-based with no committal all-in from either side.","Level 3 remains close though MF's Double Up starts out-poking you.","Levels 4-5 stay a coin-flip decided by whether you dodge her Q bounces.","At 6 MF's Bullet Time plus support CC gives her a zoning all-in your thin stacks can't answer.","At one item MF's poke build sieges you off the wave before your stacks compound.","With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting out-scale MF's stationary channel and flip the lane."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"nilah","win":["Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Nilah","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nilah is an all-in melee lane bully: she W (Jubilant Veil) to dodge your Q and autos, dashes with E (Slipstream) through minions, and lifesteals back up in every trade. Never step forward to CS when her W is up, hug tower, and only let your support engage if it hard-locks her; your thin early stacks lose the brawl."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nilah's Apotheosis ult gives her a shared-heal teamfight AoE plus her E-Q pull, a devastating 2v2 all-in while your stacks are far from the execute. Hold Achooo! purely to disengage her dash, respect the W damage-reduction window, and do not get pulled into her and her support."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her first-item spike (Immortal Shieldbow/BorK-style) with built-in lifesteal and W dodge lets her run you down before your Q count matters. This is her deepest advantage window; farm at max range, ping for jungle help, and just survive to your item-two power."},{"when":"Late","text":"You finally flip once your Q nears the 225 execute and you can kite: Nilah is short-ranged and must dash in, so space behind your frontline, save Achooo! and Flash for her E, and your compounding stacks shred her before Apotheosis heals matter."}],"wants":{"you":["To survive her lane-bully window and reach the execute stack threshold","Hugging tower and farming at max range away from her dashes","Late fights where you kite her short range behind your frontline"],"foe":["Melee all-ins with W dodging your Q and lifesteal sustaining trades","Her Apotheosis and E pull to lock you in a 2v2 all-in","A CC support to guarantee her dash connects before you kite"]},"early":"Nilah owns levels 1-4: her W dodges your Q, her E dashes onto you, and lifesteal wins every trade, so never step up when W is up and hug tower to farm. Your thin stacks can't contest, scale safely.","mid":"From 6 through her first item Nilah's Apotheosis and E pull make her a lethal all-in while your stacks are immature; hold Achooo! to disengage her dash and farm at max range. Ping for help and survive this window.","late":"With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting flip it: space behind your frontline, save Achooo!/Flash for her Slipstream, and shred her short-range body before her ult heals matter.","whys":["Level 1 Nilah bullies with her W dodge and dash-in melee trade pattern.","Level 2 Nilah stays ahead as her lifesteal wins every short trade.","Level 3 Nilah's E-Q all-in threat controls the lane against your thin stacks.","Levels 4-5 Nilah keeps snowballing her melee dominance while you can only farm.","At 6 Nilah's Apotheosis and E pull give her a lethal 2v2 all-in you can't answer.","At one item Nilah's lifesteal spike lets her run you down before your stacks compound.","With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting finally out-range Nilah's short-range all-in and flip the lane."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"samira","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Samira","Samira","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Samira wants to build her style meter by weaving Q autos and her W (Blade Whirl) to nullify your Q projectile, then E-dash off a minion or you to close. Don't feed her combo: keep minions between you, only step to CS, and never poke into her W window since it eats your Super Scorcher Breath. Your thin stacks lose an extended brawl."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Once Samira hits S-rank she can Inferno Trigger for a massive AoE ult, a game-ending 2v2 all-in especially with a CC support to combo off. Your Mounting Flames is up but stacks aren't threatening, so respect her all-in range, hold Achooo! to disengage her E, and never fight into her W-then-ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Samira's first-item spike (BorK/Shieldbow) plus lifesteal lets her dash in, weave her combo, and ult you down before your Q count matures. This is her deepest window; farm from max range, don't give her a wall to E onto you, and survive rather than duel."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale once your Q nears the 225 execute and you can kite from range: Samira must dash into melee, so space behind your frontline, save Achooo!/Flash for her E, and don't clump so her ult can't multi-hit. Your compounding stacks delete her before she resets her combo."}],"wants":{"you":["To deny her style meter and survive to stack maturity","Farming at max range so she has no minion or you to E-dash onto","Late fights where you kite her forced-melee combo behind frontline"],"foe":["Weaving her combo and using W to nullify your Q and autos","Reaching S-rank to land Inferno Trigger as a 2v2 all-in","Her lifesteal item spike plus a CC support to lock her dash-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill-based but Samira controls tempo: her W eats your Q and her E closes gaps, so keep minions between you, only step to last-hit, and never poke into her Blade Whirl. Deny her style meter and scale.","mid":"From 6 through her first item Samira is ahead: S-rank Inferno Trigger plus support CC is a lethal all-in while your stacks are thin. Respect her dash range, hold Achooo! to disengage, and farm safe.","late":"With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting flip it: space behind your frontline, save escapes for her E, spread out against her ult, and matured stacks shred her forced-melee body.","whys":["Level 1 is even before Samira's combo and style meter come online.","Level 2 stays skill-based with no committal all-in from either side.","Level 3 remains close though her W-negates-Q pattern starts edging trades.","Levels 4-5 stay a coin-flip decided by whether you deny her E-dash and style meter.","At 6 Samira's S-rank Inferno Trigger plus support CC gives her a lethal all-in your thin stacks can't answer.","At one item Samira's lifesteal spike lets her combo you down before your stacks compound.","With two-plus items your execute Q and kiting out-range Samira's forced-melee all-in and flip the lane."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Senna out-ranges you and pokes with Q (Piercing Darkness) landed through minions or an ally, harassing you off the wave while she farms soul stacks for scaling range and crit. She roots you with E-fed engages and her long autos deny your last-hits, so respect her range, only step to CS, and don't get chunked below her poke threshold."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Senna's global Dawning Shadow ult lets her shield her team or snipe you and swing skirmishes across the map, while your Mounting Flames is up but your stacks are still thin. She'll keep poking with her growing range, so play safe, hold Achooo! for disengage, and don't over-commit into her long-range harass."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where you start flipping: your Q stacks are compounding toward the execute while Senna, often built support-utility, does less raw DPS in a 2v2. Farm up, punish her if she steps to poke by W-dashing in with your support, and your damage begins to out-pace her scaling."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hard out-scale a utility Senna: your matured Q execute and Achooo! kiting turn every fight your way while she leans on shields and snipes rather than sustained damage. Space behind frontline, focus through her poke, and your 225-stack payoff deletes her carries."}],"wants":{"you":["To survive her long-range poke and reach stack maturity","Punishing her with a W-dash all-in when she steps up to Q you","Late fights where your execute DPS out-scales her utility kit"],"foe":["Out-ranging and poking you off the wave while she stacks souls","Her global Dawning Shadow to swing skirmishes and snipe you","To play a utility-shield game and deny your stacks with her range"]},"early":"Senna owns levels 1-5: she out-ranges you, pokes with Piercing Darkness through minions, and denies your CS while stacking souls. Respect her range, only step to last-hit, and don't get chunked; you're scaling and can't contest her early poke.","mid":"Through 6 Senna's growing range and global ult keep her ahead while your stacks are thin; play safe, hold Achooo! to disengage, and farm rather than trade into her long-range harass.","late":"From one item on you flip it: your compounding Q execute and kiting out-scale a utility Senna, so punish her step-ups, space behind frontline, and your matured stacks close out fights.","whys":["Level 1 Senna out-ranges you and pokes you off the wave as she stacks souls.","Level 2 Senna's Q harass and long autos keep denying your last-hits.","Level 3 Senna controls the lane with range and root-fed engages against your thin stacks.","Levels 4-5 Senna keeps poking you below threshold while you can only farm.","At 6 Senna's global Dawning Shadow and growing range keep her ahead of your immature stacks.","At one item your compounding Q stacks begin out-pacing a utility-built Senna's DPS.","With two-plus items your matured execute Q and kiting hard out-scale Senna's utility kit."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Seraphine","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have all three abilities you can weave Q into last-hits and use E's dash to reset a poke trade, but Seraphine out-ranges your early Q so bait her Q (High Note) and W shield before you step up. Farm safely and bank Dragon Practice stacks rather than forcing all-ins into her passive double-cast."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Seraphine spikes hardest here: her R Encore can charm your whole side of the lane and set up a support all-in, so respect it and hold your E flap as the escape when you see her walk up for the ult angle. Your R Mouth to Mouth is a heal/dash tool, not a duel-winner yet, so don't trade ults into her CC chain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Completing your first crit/on-hit item flips tempo — your stacked Q now clears waves and pokes from max range, letting you last-hit under tower safely and chip Seraphine when she steps up to shield. Space behind your minions so her skillshot Q and E root land on the wave, not you."},{"when":"Late","text":"With two-plus items and a fat Dragon Practice stack count, your Q becomes an execute cannon that outranges Encore's cast — punish any Seraphine who front-lines. Kite backward on her R cooldown and delete her before she reloads her shields."}],"wants":{"you":["Stacks banked so your Q out-ranges her poke","Her R Encore burned before you commit","Sidelane space to farm and scale safely"],"foe":["Landing charm from Q or R into a support engage","Poking you off the wave with High Note before you stack","Grouping 5v5 where her shields and CC shine"]},"early":"Even and skill-based at L1-2: neither of you wants to shove, so trade autos on her cooldowns, dodge her Q, and focus on clean last-hits to start banking Dragon Practice stacks.","mid":"L3-6 stays a farm-and-poke lane you can play, but at 6 Seraphine's Encore charm plus a support engage is the real threat — hold E to disengage and don't duel into her ult.","late":"Post-first-item you take over: your stacked Q out-ranges her whole kit, so poke her off the wave, kite her R, and scale into an unkillable late-game monster.","whys":["Level 1 is even — both of you just soak XP and last-hit with no real trade pattern.","Level 2 is skill-dependent — whoever lands the first clean auto-trade edges it, not a kit advantage.","Level 3 stays even as both fish for cooldown trades and neither can hard-commit.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill lane where positioning and dodging her Q decide small trades.","Level 6 favors Seraphine because Encore's AoE charm enables a support all-in you can't yet answer.","First item flips it to you as your stacked Q out-ranges and out-damages her poke.","With 2+ items your Q execute and range make you the clear late-game winner over her shields."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Sivir","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sivir owns the early lane: her Q Boomerang Blade pokes through minions and her W Ricochet lets her shove and bounce onto you while you're stuck last-hitting. Hold your E flap for when she over-extends on a wave-clear and don't walk into Q range — soak the poke, bank Dragon Practice stacks, and accept you're behind on tempo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R On the Hunt gives her whole team move speed for an engage or disengage, so a Sivir-enabled all-in with her support is dangerous while your stacks are low. Your R Mouth to Mouth heals but won't win the fight yet — play for XP, use E to break the speed-boosted chase, and avoid trading into her E Spell Shield windows."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is the turning point: a stacked Q now out-ranges her Boomerang and clears waves without walking up, so you stop feeding her Ricochet shove. Space behind minions so her Q only hits creeps and start pushing the poke war back in your favor."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items and a high stack count your Q executes from beyond her range — the only thing she can do is Spell Shield one cast, so bait it with a small Q before your big one. Kite her shove and you win every extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach a completed first item with stacks banked","Bait her E Spell Shield before your key Q","Space so her Q hits minions, not you"],"foe":["Shoving with W Ricochet to lock you under tower","Poking you low with Q before you scale","Using R speed to enable an early all-in"]},"early":"Sivir wins L1-2 outright — her Q pokes through the wave and W lets her shove and control tempo while you can only last-hit and eat chip damage.","mid":"L3-6 stays Sivir's lane: she shoves you in, pokes with Boomerang, and her R speed enables ganks and all-ins before your stacks come online, so play safe and farm.","late":"Once your first item lands the poke war inverts — your stacked Q out-ranges her whole kit, you bait her Spell Shield, and you scale into an unstoppable late game.","whys":["Level 1 favors Sivir — her Q pokes through minions while you can only soak XP.","Level 2 stays Sivir's as W Ricochet lets her shove and dictate the wave.","Level 3 favors Sivir because she out-ranges and out-tempos your unstacked kit.","Levels 4-5 remain hers — her poke and shove keep you pinned and low.","Level 6 favors Sivir since R On the Hunt speed enables an all-in you can't yet survive.","First item flips it to you as your stacked Q finally out-ranges her Boomerang.","With 2+ items your Q execute and range beat her Spell Shield and win every fight."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Smolder","Swain","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain bot is a poke-and-pull threat: his W Vision of Empire and E Nevermore root can lock you for a support all-in, so respect his E line and don't stand in obvious spots. Weave Q into last-hits, hold E flap to dodge his root, and bank Dragon Practice stacks — the lane is skill-based and you can trade back when his E is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your window: Swain's R Demonic Ascension only spikes once he's stacked souls and in melee range, and at 6 you can burst him with a stacked Q before he ramps. Punish him when his E is on cooldown, but keep E ready — his ult heals hard if he pulls you in with a support, so trade then disengage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Swain's first item (often a tank/AP support-style build with Rylai's or Liandry's) makes his R sustain and slow oppressive in extended fights, so don't sit in his ult radius. Poke him with max-range Q, back off before he channels Demonic Ascension, and use minions to block his E root."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items your Q execute and E mobility let you kite Swain's slow-moving ult entirely — he can't catch you and can't out-DPS your stacked Q. Space at max range, dodge the E, and delete him before his soul fragments matter."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish him at 6 before his R ramps","Dodge his E Nevermore root with minions or flap","Bank stacks so your Q bursts him first"],"foe":["Landing E root into a support all-in","Ramping R Demonic Ascension in an extended fight","Poking you with W and sustaining through trades"]},"early":"Skill lane at L1-2: Swain wants to land E and poke with W, so dodge his root, dodge his line, and trade on his cooldowns while you start stacking.","mid":"L3-6 stays skill-based, then at 6 you edge ahead — you can burst Swain with a stacked Q before his ult ramps, so punish his E cooldowns while holding flap for his all-in.","late":"Swain's first-item R sustain briefly out-values you in extended fights, but with 2+ items your Q range and E kiting leave his slow ult grasping air — you win the late game clean.","whys":["Level 1 is even — both farm and neither can commit without a clear opening.","Level 2 stays skill-based as you fish for trades around his E cooldown.","Level 3 remains even; his root threat and your poke cancel out.","Levels 4-5 are still a skill lane decided by dodging his E and W.","Level 6 favors you — a stacked Q bursts Swain before his R can ramp its soul stacks.","First item favors Swain as his R sustain and slow out-value you in extended trades.","With 2+ items your Q execute and E kiting outrange his slow ult and win the late game."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Tristana","Tristana","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early it's a skill lane: Tristana's short base range means she can't poke you freely, so trade autos when her E Explosive Charge isn't stacked on you and weave Q into last-hits. Watch her W Rocket Jump — if she jumps in she's committing, so hold your E flap to disengage or to punish her landing before she can reset."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Tristana pulls ahead here: her W reset on kills plus R Buster Shot gives her a jump-in-burst-knockback all-in that, with a support, can blow you up before your stacks matter. Respect the W range, don't stand on low HP near her, and hold E and R Mouth to Mouth purely as escape tools rather than trading into her burst combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her power peaks around first item — a Rapid Firecannon or lethality Trist jumps, stacks E, and detonates for a kill, so play behind minions and keep your flap up. Farm safely, avoid the all-in, and keep banking Dragon Practice stacks because your payoff comes later than hers."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items the range war inverts hard: your stacked Q out-ranges her W jump and executes her before she lands her E detonation. Kite backward when she jumps, drop her with Q, and she has no follow-up — you dominate every late fight and teamfight."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive to 2+ items with stacks banked","Punish her W Rocket Jump commitment with flap","Kite her jump and execute with max-range Q"],"foe":["Landing a W-jump E-detonate all-in around first item","Getting W resets to snowball the lane","Using R Buster Shot to secure or peel a kill"]},"early":"Skill lane at L1-2 — Tristana's short range keeps her from poking, so trade on her E windows, respect a committal W jump, and start stacking cleanly.","mid":"L3-6 flips to Tristana: her W reset plus R Buster Shot all-in with a support can burst you before your stacks come online, so play safe, hold flap, and farm.","late":"Once you hit 2+ items the matchup inverts — your stacked Q out-ranges her jump and executes her, and she has no answer to your kiting in extended fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even — her short range denies poke and you both just farm.","Level 2 stays skill-based, decided by trading around her E stacks.","Level 3 remains even as neither can safely hard-commit yet.","Levels 4-5 are a skill lane where dodging her W-jump timing matters most.","Level 6 favors Tristana — W reset plus R Buster Shot give her a burst all-in you can't yet survive.","First item stays Tristana's as her jump-detonate combo peaks before your stacks pay off.","With 2+ items your Q out-ranges her jump and executes her, winning the late game outright."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch is the scarier lane bully early: his Q Ambush stealth plus E Contaminate lets him roam invisible and burst you when his poison stacks are high, so ward your flanks and never sit at low HP. Farm at max range, hold your E flap for when he decloaks on you, and bank Dragon Practice stacks — you cannot win the early trade war so don't try."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Twitch spikes hard at 6: R Spray and Pray gives him piercing long-range autos that shred you and your support in any extended fight or all-in. Keep vision on his stealth approach, don't group tightly, and use E and R Mouth to Mouth to disengage rather than trading into his ult-boosted DPS window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His first item (often Runaan's or a crit spike) plus E Contaminate detonation makes his burst lethal, so respect the invisible engage and play behind minions. Your stacked Q is starting to out-range him — poke when he's revealed and back off before his six-stack Contaminate detonates."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items you flip it: your stacked Q executes Twitch from beyond his effective range, and he's a squishy, immobile target once revealed. Hold E to dodge his engage, punish him the instant his stealth drops, and kite his R DPS with pure distance."}],"wants":{"you":["Vision to deny his stealth engage","Reach 2+ items with stacks banked","Punish him the moment he decloaks with max-range Q"],"foe":["Ambushing from stealth into a Contaminate burst","Ramping R Spray and Pray in an extended fight","Poking you low with poison stacks before you scale"]},"early":"Twitch owns L1-2 — his stealth and poison-stack poke let him control the lane and threaten a burst all-in while you can only farm and ward.","mid":"L3-6 stays Twitch's lane: his Ambush engage and, at 6, R Spray and Pray shred you before your stacks come online, so play safe, keep vision, and hold flap.","late":"Once your first item lands and stacks pile up, your Q out-ranges and executes a squishy Twitch — you kite his DPS, punish his decloak, and win every late fight.","whys":["Level 1 favors Twitch — his stealth and poison poke let him bully you off the wave.","Level 2 stays Twitch's as his Ambush engage threat keeps you pinned.","Level 3 favors Twitch because Contaminate burst out-trades your unstacked kit.","Levels 4-5 remain his — his roam and poke keep you low and reactive.","Level 6 favors Twitch since R Spray and Pray shreds you in any extended fight.","First item flips it to you as your stacked Q begins to out-range his effective DPS.","With 2+ items your Q executes a squishy Twitch and you kite his ult with pure distance."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"varus","win":["Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Varus","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Varus out-pokes you early: his charged Q Piercing Arrow and W Blighted Quiver stacks let him chunk you from max range while you're stuck last-hitting under pressure. Dodge his Q charge by staying behind minions, hold E flap for when he steps up to detonate blight stacks, and just soak XP while banking Dragon Practice stacks — you lose the poke war until you scale."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Varus's R Chain of Corruption is a long-range root that sets up a support all-in and can catch you flat-footed, so respect his ult angle and don't stand in the open. Your R Mouth to Mouth is escape, not a duel tool yet — hold E to break his root chase and avoid trading into a blight-stack detonation while his poke lead is real."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first item is the swing: a stacked Q now matches and out-ranges his Piercing Arrow, so the poke war inverts and you can chunk him when he charges up. Space behind the wave so his Q only hits minions, bait his R, and start farming freely as your scaling kicks in."},{"when":"Late","text":"With 2+ items and a huge stack count your Q executes from beyond his charged Q range — Varus is immobile, so once his R root is down he simply can't fight you. Kite backward, dodge the arrow, and delete him; this is a hard-winning late game reflected in your fat win rate."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach first item with stacks banked to out-range his Q","Bait or dodge his R Chain of Corruption","Space so his charged Q hits minions, not you"],"foe":["Poking you down with charged Q and blight stacks","Landing R root into a support all-in","Winning the lane before your scaling comes online"]},"early":"Varus dominates L1-2 poke — his charged Q and blight stacks chunk you from range while you can only last-hit and soak the damage.","mid":"L3-6 stays Varus's lane: his poke keeps you low and his R root at 6 enables an all-in before your stacks matter, so play safe, dodge arrows, and farm.","late":"Once your first item lands you take over hard — your stacked Q out-ranges his Piercing Arrow, you bait his root, and by 2+ items you execute an immobile Varus every fight.","whys":["Level 1 favors Varus — his charged Q pokes you from beyond your range.","Level 2 stays Varus's as blight stacks let him chunk you on every trade.","Level 3 favors Varus because his sustained poke out-values your unstacked kit.","Levels 4-5 remain his — he keeps you low and pinned with arrow poke.","Level 6 favors Varus since R Chain of Corruption root enables a support all-in.","First item flips it to you as your stacked Q out-ranges his Piercing Arrow.","With 2+ items your Q executes an immobile Varus and you win the late game hard."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Smolder","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vayne has no waveclear and can't answer your Q (Super Scorcher Breath) poke, so you should be building early stacks and denying her farm; the lane is even only because a good Vayne can Q (Tumble) an auto-reset onto you when you step up to last-hit, so respect her all-in windows if her Condemn is up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your ult (Mouthful of Terror) is online and Vayne's still a scaling shell with no range; you hold the level-6 edge because a stacked Q plus dragon breath out-trades her before her Silver Bolts can proc three times, and you punish any Tumble-in with a big empowered Q."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard on your first item and stack count while Vayne is still one item from being relevant; keep spacing behind minions so her Condemn only hits a wall, and burn her down before she gets Q resets going."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne out-scales most ADCs into ultra-late, but with a healthy stack lead your Q one-shots and dragon-breath AoE let you delete her before she can weave Tumbles; never let her isolate you in a side bush where Condemn stuns."}],"wants":{"you":["Stack Q early on the wave and on Vayne to snowball your damage before she scales","Space behind your minions so Condemn (E) has a wall but never pins you","Punish every Tumble-forward last-hit with an empowered Q trade"],"foe":["Reach 2-3 items so Silver Bolts and Q resets carry a fight","Catch you out of position to Condemn you into a wall for the stun","Use Tumble invisibility windows to close and burst you in melee range"]},"early":"Vayne has no poke and no waveclear, so at levels 1-2 the lane is a skill check: you want to CS freely and land Q pokes, but a sharp Vayne can Tumble-auto onto you when you overstep, so trade on your terms and keep your support's CC in mind for her all-in.","mid":"By levels 3-6 you pull ahead — you're stacking Q and gaining range and burst while Vayne is still short-range with no wave control; hold the level-6 timing because your ult plus a fed Q out-damages her three-shot pattern, and every Condemn she misses into a minion is free tempo for you.","late":"On one item and beyond your stacks make you the faster-scaling threat in this specific duel; punish Vayne before she completes two items, keep her out of side bushes where Condemn stuns, and in teamfights delete her with a max-stack Q before Silver Bolts ever ramp.","whys":["No poke and no waveclear from Vayne, but her Tumble auto-reset all-in keeps L1 a skill check.","Neither of you spikes at 2; a good Vayne Tumble trade balances your Q poke.","Level 3 is even — your Q chip versus her Condemn all-in threat cancel out.","Through 4-5 it stays skill-based: you farm and poke, she looks for a Tumble catch.","At 6 your ult and stacked Q out-trade Vayne's un-scaled three-shot pattern.","Your first-item plus stacks spike lands while Vayne is still one item from relevance.","Your stack lead lets you delete Vayne before her late-game Silver Bolts carry."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Veigar","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Veigar bullies you early with Baleful Strike (Q) poke that also stacks his AP infinitely, so every trade he wins farms his scaling; his Dark Matter (W) zones your last-hits and Event Horizon (E) cage can lock you for a full combo, so you're behind and must farm safe rather than force stacks under threat of his burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Veigar's ult (Primordial Burst) comes online and can chunk or delete you from range, so level 6 is his — don't stand in E-cage range without your support's peel, and use your dragon-breath dashes and range to dodge Dark Matter while you keep farming toward your own spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"The lane flips on your first item: your Q stacks plus completed damage let you out-DPS a squishy Veigar who has to land E to kill you; walk up behind minions so Event Horizon catches creeps, and once his cage is on cooldown you win the trade every time."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, Veigar one-shots if he lands E into ult, but your stacked Q gives you the range and burst to blow him up first or from outside cage range; never face-check his Event Horizon, kite around it, and delete him before he re-cages."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the early poke and farm stacks safely until your first item spike","Dodge Event Horizon (E) so he can't land his Dark Matter and ult combo","Out-range and out-DPS a squishy Veigar once your Q stacks come online"],"foe":["Land Baleful Strike (Q) last-hits to stack AP and out-scale you","Cage you with Event Horizon (E) into Dark Matter and Primordial Burst","Reach his own item and stack thresholds to one-shot you from range"]},"early":"Veigar owns levels 1-2: his Baleful Strike pokes you and permanently stacks his AP, so trading into him literally feeds his scaling; you have no kill pressure yet, so focus on safe CS, dodge Dark Matter, and don't get greedy for stacks while his burst threatens you.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 you're still behind — Dark Matter zones your farm and his Event Horizon cage plus level-6 Primordial Burst can delete you if you misposition; play behind minions, save dashes to break the cage, and just scale, because forcing fights into a fed Veigar loses.","late":"On one completed item and with Q stacks the duel swings to you: you have more sustained DPS and range than a glass Veigar who needs to land a single E to kill you. Kite around Event Horizon, punish it on cooldown, and burst him from outside cage range in fights before he can chain his combo.","whys":["Veigar's Baleful Strike poke stacks his AP and bullies you at level 1.","At 2 his Q chip and Dark Matter zone keep the early tempo his.","Level 3 Event Horizon cage threat gives Veigar the trading edge.","Through 4-5 his poke-and-stack pattern keeps you farming behind.","Level 6 Primordial Burst lets Veigar delete you from range — clearly his.","Your first item plus Q stacks flip the lane; you out-DPS a squishy Veigar.","Late, your stacked-Q range and burst kill him before he re-cages."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Xayah out-trades you early with Double Daggers (Q) and stacked feathers she can Bladecaller (E) root you with, and her lane push plus Deadly Plumage attack-speed steroid means she wins extended trades; you're behind, so farm carefully, don't stand on her ground feathers, and stack Q for your later spike."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Xayah's Featherstorm (R) gives her invulnerability and a huge feather setup for a root, so level 6 is hers on the all-in; respect that she can dodge your ult and support CC with R, hold your engage, and keep spacing until your first item lets you out-DPS her."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On your first item plus Q stacks you flip the DPS lead: Xayah is a straight-up carry with no innate escape besides R, so once her Featherstorm is down you out-range and out-burst her; punish her by fighting when R is on cooldown and never clumping into her feather lines."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, Xayah has strong AoE feather burst and a root, but your stacked Q out-damages and out-ranges her; the whole game is watching her Featherstorm — bait or wait it out, then delete her, and don't get rooted by a Bladecaller from feathers you walked over."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the early feather trades and stack Q toward your item spike","Avoid standing on her ground feathers so Bladecaller (E) can't root you","Fight when Featherstorm (R) is down and out-range her with stacked Q"],"foe":["Win early extended trades with Deadly Plumage (W) and Double Daggers","Set up feathers and Bladecaller (E) root into her all-in","Use Featherstorm (R) to dodge your ult and support CC then burst you"]},"early":"Xayah takes levels 1-2: Double Daggers and her feather setup give her a stronger auto-trade and lane push, so stepping up to last-hit into her means eating a Q and risking a Bladecaller root; play safe CS, dodge her ground feathers, and start stacking for your spike.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Xayah-favoured — her Deadly Plumage steroid wins extended fights and her level-6 Featherstorm can invuln through your ult and your support's CC; don't force the all-in, keep your positioning clean of feather lines, and just scale toward your first item.","late":"Once your first item lands and your Q is stacked the duel is yours: you have more range and burst than Xayah, whose only defensive tool is Featherstorm. Track her R, fight when it's down, avoid walking over feathers that let her root you, and in teamfights blow her up before she can plumage-and-feather your backline.","whys":["Xayah's Double Daggers and feather setup win the level-1 auto-trade.","At 2 her Deadly Plumage steroid and lane push keep tempo hers.","Level 3 feather-into-Bladecaller root threat gives Xayah the edge.","Through 4-5 her stronger extended trades keep you farming behind.","Level 6 Featherstorm invuln and root setup make the all-in hers.","Your first item plus Q stacks flip it — you out-DPS a no-escape Xayah.","Late, your stacked-Q range and burst kill her once Featherstorm is down."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Zeri","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri pokes you down with her Burst Fire (Q) auto-attacks and her Ultrashock Laser (W) piercing slow, and her mobility lets her dance in and out of your Q range; she wins early because she chips you safely while you're trying to land skillshot Q, so farm patiently and don't chase her."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zeri's Lightning Crash (R) turns her into a hyper-mobile DPS threat and lets her all-in or disengage at will, so level 6 is hers; don't over-extend expecting a kill, respect that she can wall-dash away from your ult and support CC, and keep stacking toward your spike."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You flip on your first item and stack count: Zeri ramps but is squishy and relies on hitting her Q stream, so once you're itemized your bigger single-target Q burst out-trades her; punish her when her R is down and force fights where she can't kite freely."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, Zeri scales into a monster if she snowballs, but with a healthy stack lead your Q out-damages her per-shot; the key is she can wall-dash and reposition, so catch her Lightning Crash cooldowns, don't let her isolate-kite you, and burst her before her Crash ramps."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm through the early poke and stack Q toward your first-item spike","Fight Zeri when Lightning Crash (R) is down and she can't kite freely","Land your stacked Q burst on a squishy Zeri before her ramp gets going"],"foe":["Chip you with Burst Fire (Q) and Ultrashock Laser (W) while kiting safely","Use her mobility and wall-dashes to dodge your Q and support CC","Snowball Lightning Crash (R) ramp into an unkillable DPS state"]},"early":"Zeri takes levels 1-2: her Burst Fire auto-poke and Ultrashock Laser slow let her chip you while staying out of your skillshot Q range, and her passive shield eats your pokes; play for safe CS, don't chase her mobility, and start stacking rather than forcing bad trades.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Zeri's — her sustained poke and slows wear you down, and level-6 Lightning Crash gives her the mobility to all-in or escape your ult and support CC; don't over-commit, space behind minions, and just scale toward your first item where the lane flips.","late":"On one item with Q stacks you take over: Zeri is squishy and reliant on kiting, and your stacked single-target Q burst out-trades her ramp. Track her Lightning Crash windows, fight when it's down, deny her the space to wall-dash-kite you, and in fights delete her before her Crash and attack-speed stacks spiral out of control.","whys":["Zeri's Burst Fire poke and slow chip you while dodging your skillshot Q.","At 2 her sustained poke and passive shield keep the tempo hers.","Level 3 her mobility and Ultrashock slow keep her safely ahead in poke.","Through 4-5 her kite-and-chip pattern keeps you farming behind.","Level 6 Lightning Crash mobility lets Zeri all-in or escape at will.","Your first item plus Q stacks flip it — you out-burst a squishy Zeri.","Late, your stacked-Q per-shot burst kills her before her Crash ramps."]},
  {"a":"smolder_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ziggs","Smolder","Smolder"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs sits back and lobs Bouncing Bomb (Q) to zone your last-hits and shove the wave, but he has no all-in and you can dodge his skillshots while stacking Q; the lane is even here because his poke is answered by your own range and dash mobility, so weave around his bombs and farm your stacks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ziggs' Mega Inferno Bomb (R) gives him lane-wide and cross-map poke and a wave-clear that keeps you off farm, so level 6 tips to him; respect his Satchel Charge (W) knockback that can peel your all-in, and keep dodging his AoE while you scale toward your item."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You flip on your first item and stack count: Ziggs is a stationary artillery mage with only Satchel to escape, so once you're itemized your Q burst and dragon-breath dashes let you close and delete him; punish him when Satchel is down and force him off his comfortable poke range."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, Ziggs offers strong AoE zone and poke but folds to a diver, and your stacked Q plus mobility let you gap-close and one-shot him; watch his Satchel knockback and Minefield slow, don't eat a full R, and blow him up before he can chunk your team from range."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke while stacking Q toward your item spike","Use your dash mobility to close the gap once you're itemized","Punish Ziggs when Satchel Charge (W) is down and he can't self-peel"],"foe":["Zone your farm and shove waves with Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke","Keep you off CS with Mega Inferno Bomb (R) and Hexplosive Minefield","Use Satchel Charge (W) knockback to peel your all-in and escape"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill check: Ziggs lobs Bouncing Bomb to zone your last-hits and push the wave, but he has zero kill pressure and you can dodge his skillshots while poking back and stacking; walk up behind minions, weave around his bombs, and farm cleanly since neither of you can commit a kill.","mid":"Through levels 3-6 it stays even until his ult — you trade pokes and dodge bombs while stacking, but level-6 Mega Inferno Bomb gives Ziggs lane-wide zone and waveclear that keeps you off farm and can poke you pre-fight; play around his Satchel peel, keep dodging, and scale to your first item.","late":"On one item with Q stacks you take over: Ziggs is immobile artillery with only Satchel to escape, and your stacked Q burst plus dragon-breath dashes let you dive and delete him. Fight when his Satchel is down, avoid eating a full Mega Inferno Bomb, and in teamfights gap-close onto him before he zones your backline.","whys":["Ziggs zones with Bouncing Bomb but has no all-in — L1 is a skill check.","At 2 his poke-and-shove is answered by your range and dodging; still even.","Level 3 stays skill-based: his bombs versus your dash mobility cancel out.","Through 4-5 you trade pokes and dodge evenly while both scale.","Level 6 Mega Inferno Bomb gives Ziggs lane-wide zone and waveclear — his.","Your first item plus Q stacks flip it — you dive an immobile Ziggs.","Late, your stacked-Q burst and dashes delete him before he zones your team."]}
